1.	To compile:
		$ make
	(if this fails, you may want to try GNU make)

2.	Now put the resulting file "tcpcgi.cgi" on your webserver some
	place that it can be executed as a CGI.

3.	Run "tcpcgi" on your local machine with the proper options.
	(see USAGE for information on the arguments)

4.	Connect to your local machine on the port specified in "tcpcgi"
	and use as normal.
